Creating & setting custom theme


theme_viny_bright <- function(){
  
  library(ggthemes)
  
  ggthemes::theme_fivethirtyeight() %+replace%
  
  theme(
    axis.title = element_text(),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 8),
    legend.text = element_text(size = 10),
    panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white"),
    plot.background = element_rect(fill = "white"),
    strip.background = element_blank(),
    legend.background = element_rect(fill = NA),
    legend.key = element_rect(fill = NA),
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5,
                              size = 19,
                              face = "bold"),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5)
      )
  
  }

theme_set(theme_viny_bright())

           month = factor(month, levels = month.abb), # this will sort the months
           month = factor(month))  # this will drop two unused levels - Jan, Feb

data %>% 
  select(where(is.factor)) %>% 
  
  imap(function(feature_value, feature_name) {
    
    count(data.frame(x = feature_value), x) %>% 
    mutate(x = fct_reorder(x, n)) %>% 
      
      ggplot(aes(x = x, y = n)) +
      geom_col() +
      coord_flip() +
      labs(title = feature_name)
  })

Variable Analysis function

Composite_function <- function(data, y_var = age, var_name){
  var_name = enquo(var_name)
  
# Create a basic bar
pie <- ggplot(data %>% count(!!var_name) %>% mutate(n = n / sum(n)), 
             aes(x="", y=n, fill=!!var_name)) + 
  geom_bar(stat="identity", width=1, alpha = 0.9) + 
  coord_polar("y", start=0) +
  geom_text(aes(label = paste0(levels(as.factor(!!var_name)),":\n", round(n*100, digits = 1), "%")), 
                                        position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5), size = 3.5) +
 
# Add color scale (hex colors)
# scale_fill_manual(values=c("#55DDE0", "#33658A", "#2F4858", "#F6AE2D", "#F26419", "#999999")) +
  # scale_fill_manual(values = c("midnightblue","tomato")) +
 
  labs(x = NULL, y = NULL, fill = NULL, title = glue("{quo_name(var_name)} Proportions")) + 
  theme_classic() + 
  theme(axis.line = element_blank(),
          axis.text = element_blank(),
          axis.ticks = element_blank(),
          plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, color = "#666666", size = 12, face="bold"),
        legend.position = "none"
          )

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- #


Bar <- data %>% 
    group_by(!!var_name, y) %>% 
    summarise(n = n()) %>% 
    
    ggplot(aes(x = !!var_name, y = n, fill = y)) +
    geom_col(position = "dodge", alpha = 0.9) +
    # labs(title = glue("y count of {quo_name(var_name)}")) + 
  theme(
    legend.position = c(1, .98),
    legend.justification = c("right", "top"),
    legend.box.just = "right",
    # legend.margin = margin(6, 6, 6, 6),
    legend.direction = "vertical", 
    legend.text = element_text(size =7), legend.key.size = unit(.3,'cm'), legend.title = element_text(size=9),
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, color = "#666666", size = 12, face="bold"),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 7), axis.title = element_text(size = 9)
    ) +
  guides(x = guide_axis(n.dodge = 2))


# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- #


violin <- ggplot() +
  gghalves::geom_half_violin(data = data %>% 
                               filter(y=="yes") %>%

  gghalves::geom_half_violin(data = data %>% 
                               filter(y=="no") %>%

                             mapping = aes(x = !!var_name, y = {{y_var}}, fill = y), 
                             alpha = 0.9, side = "r"
                             ) +
  # scale_x_discrete(labels = c("Non Seniors","Senior Citizen")) +
  # labs(title = glue("Monthly Charges distribution by {quo_name(var_name)}")) + 
  # scale_y_continuous(labels = dollar_format()) +
  theme(
    legend.position = c(1, .98),
    legend.justification = c("right", "top"),
    legend.box.just = "right",
    # legend.margin = margin(6, 6, 6, 6),
    legend.direction = "vertical",

    )
